
[1]regale

   REGA'LE, n. The prerogative of monarchy.

   REGA'LE, n. [See the verb, below.] A magnificent entertainment or treat
   given to embassadors and other persons of distinction.

   REGA'LE, v.t. [Eng. gale, gallant, jolly; Gr.]

   To refresh; to entertain with something that delights; to gratify, as
   the senses; as, to regale the taste, the eye or the ear. The birds of
   the forest regale us with their songs.

                REGA'LE, v.t. To feast; to fare sumptuously.
